cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on affective classification tasks using textual snippets from the HappyDB database. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper utilizes both traditional classifiers and deep learning models for classification tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of supervised and semi-supervised learning methods. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper explores social involvement and control indicators in happy moments. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper utilizes sentiment lexicons to aid in affective classification tasks.
